│ while `LegacyVF.Width` is scalable with known minimum value 4. The function │
│ `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications()` should return true if there are   │
│ simplifications in the VPlan that aren't accounted for in the legacy cost   │
│ model, but due to the nature of the test case (involving invariant          │
│ condition and select), the cost models are making different decisions       │
│ without proper justification.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis: The issue stems    │
│ from the fact that the assertion assumes that when the VPlan and legacy     │
│ cost models disagree, it must be because the VPlan contains additional      │
│ simplifications. However, in cases involving scalable vectors vs fixed      │
│ vectors, the models can legitimately disagree due to different handling of  │
│ scalable vs fixed vector types, especially when the loop contains           │
│ operations that may not benefit from vectorization (like the invariant      │
│ condition `%c.1 = icmp eq i8 %x, 0` in the reproducer).\n\n4. Proposed Edit │
│ Point(s): The assertion at lines 7522-7525 needs to be updated to handle    │
│ cases where one model selects a scalar VF and the other selects a scalable  │
